claim.claim-text:
A liquid-crystal display (100; 200), including a display area (Z1) and a shielding area (Z2) surrounding the display area, wherein the shielding area has a total transmittance of equal to or less than about 50% and greater than 0, the liquid-crystal display comprising:
a first substrate (202) including a pixel electrode and a plurality of metal traces disposed thereon, wherein the pixel electrode is disposed in the display area (Z1), and the plurality of metal trances are disposed in the shielding area (Z2) and connected to the pixel electrode;
a second substrate (204) including a light-shielding layer (214) and an opposite electrode disposed thereon, wherein the light-shielding layer is disposed in the shielding area (Z2) and adjacent to a side of the display area (Z1);
a sealant, adherently securing the first substrate and the second substrate, disposed in a sealant dispensing area (210A) and surrounding a side of light-shielding layer (214) opposite to the display area, wherein the sealant dispensing area is in the shielding area; and
a liquid-crystal layer (206) interposed between the first substrate and the second substrate and surrounded and sealed by the sealant.
